children.text: ※If there is question, please confirm with Tenant Coordinator.
※This Checklist must use when as built . If found the problem quickly improve do it.
6.	Near void area - furniture must be fixed and maximum height is 1400mm only

7.	Tempered or laminated glass is only allowed 10mm minimum thickness).
The thickness of glass adjusted upon the heights and complied with design guideline.
8.	Planter box is also provided for some areas (600mm width, 300mm setback to both from lease line)
9.	F&B Tenant must provide waiting seat
1.	Divider wall area, must setback 200mm and follow leaseline
2.	Façade opening required minimum 50% (total front façade width)
3.	Control zone area - must be see through (1200mm maximum height & 1350mm on the handrail area)
4.	Ceiling height - must follow each regulation minimum height required
5.	Signage detail, height & location must follow each regulation (must have lighting)
5.	All furniture has no sharp edges
3.	Hanging Signages, suspended ceiling must have proper support
4.	All Hand rail & funiture must fix from slab
1.	All interior and exterior Tenant façade must have lighting
2.	Maximum width/ thickness of signage is 100mm
2.	Fire escape route must be clear of any obstruction
1.	Must have holes/ perforation at least eye level
2.	Cannot use existing Landlord's downhung wall for support
1.	Open ceiling - to be painted except fire fighting pipes, LPG pipes, fire alarm conduit pipes, main CB, MCCB box and cable ladder/ trunking
2.	Open ceiling - down hung wall must be covered by Tenant
3.	With ceiling - must have 600 x 600mm access panel for ISOLATOR, VD (SAD,KEA,KOA,SMOKESPILL), water valve, chilled water, LPG valve, FCU unit

4.	All ceiling structure must use suspension bolt from the slab anchor.
Must not fixing A work structure frame, carefully check the slab to avoid tendon location (paint marking on slab)
1.	Tenant to provide own wall beside existing wall ("A" wall)
2.	Tenant cannot hack or drill on existing wall, column from floor to slab
3.	Tenant wall must be fire rated - in areas near fire escape corridor
4.	For areas with expansion joint - must follow expansion joint detail for walls
5.	Void and island - Tenants to follow column décor height limit

1.	Tenant floor level must be the same as the common area.
If Tenant make raise floor must make slope 1/12 for wheel chair customer.
2.	Indication of any services concealed into the Tenant floor finish (drain point,…)
3.	Raised floor to conceal drainage piping on kitchens and other areas as required. F.C.O. must be exposed
4.	All wet areas must have waterproofing. Tenant to submit ponding test report and warranty certificate
5.	For areas with expansion joint - no fixed furniture or fixtures. Must follow expansion joint detail for floor
5.	Glasswall must paste anti-collision sticker glass inside
7.	No door is allowed. Opening must be 50% of the total facade length
3.	Tenant don't exceed divider wall bulkhead. Must make own wall beside all A work wall
4.	Glasswall must paste laminate film for prevention broken glass
2.	Follow the bulkhead and downhung wall line
1.	Follow lot layout plan (must not exceed lease line)
